  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 9 airports right now. Engine anti-ice operations are flagged at Iaşi (IAS/LRIA), Craiova (CRA/LRCV). Across base airports: 3 critical, 7 high, 15 medium, 14 normal. Key bases needing attention include Chişinău (RMO/LUKK), Iaşi (IAS/LRIA) and Belgrade Nikola Tesla (BEG/LYBE); plus 7 other bases. 15 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is fog / freezing fog, RVR limitations and very low visibility  — most notably around Iaşi (IAS/LRIA), Craiova (CRA/LRCV) and Bucharest Băneasa Aurel Vlaicu (BBU/LRBS). Network hotspots: Iaşi (IAS/LRIA), Craiova (CRA/LRCV), Lennart Meri Tallinn (TLL/EETN), Turku (TKU/EFTU), Oslo-Gardermoen (OSL/ENGM) and 4 others. Primary drivers: cold‑temperature performance penalties, very low visibility and low cloud base. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 12 airports changed status, led by Iaşi (IAS/LRIA), Lennart Meri Tallinn (TLL/EETN), Turku (TKU/EFTU) and 9 others.",
